Background

		Mr. Thruston Ballard Morton, III, Thrus, is Co-Founder at Global Endowment Management, LP since March 2007 and serves as the Chief Executive Officer at the firm. He also served as the Chief Investment Officer at the firm. Previously, Mr. Morton had been the President, Chief Executive Officer and Chief Investment Officer at Duke University Management Company from 2000 to December 2006. Prior to that, he was a Managing Director at JP Morgan. Mr. Morton was a Director of ... TIFF Advisory Services, Inc. He is a member of the Finance and Investment Committee at The Rockefeller Foundation. Mr. Morton graduated, magna cum laude, with a B.A. in Southeast Asian History (honors) from Brown University, where he was elected to Phi Beta Kappa.Read Full Background




